I have implemented auto-commit in the `cleanup_scv` function within `src/adjutant/engine.py`. 

### Changes:
- **`src/adjutant/engine.py`**:
    - Updated `cleanup_scv` to check for uncommitted changes (modified, untracked, etc.) in the SCV worktree using `git status --porcelain`.
    - If changes are found, they are automatically staged and committed with the message `[SCV Auto-Commit] Work in progress before cleanup`.
    - This auto-commit happens before the branch is pushed to origin and the worktree is removed, ensuring that any stranded work by an SCV is preserved in the git history.
